fields.ai_review: The Nothing 2a phone has a clean, user-friendly interface and a surprisingly good camera for its price. Users love its design, smooth screen, and overall performance. However, the phone doesn't include a charger, forcing customers to buy one separately. Some users experienced heating issues initially, but these were resolved with an Android update.

fields.description: Fantastic phone. Charges super fast with nothing charger. Got hot in the beginning but became alright after updating the Android. Hoping to use this for a long time.

The phone is really good. I have received many compliments from people about this phone. The user experience is also very good. I like the symmetrical bezels around the screen, makes it look really premium, the screen is sharp and adequately bright, the interface is really smooth, I wouldn't say it's fast but it gets the job done, I'm coming from a OP 5T, so this phone with its 120HZ screen does look faster than my old phone, I do know it's limitations and I'm okay with the compramises made to make it a well rounded package at an affordable price. I would have given 5/5 stars, but no company is perfect. -1 star for not having a charger in the box, I had to spend an additional 2k for a compatible 45w charger on Amazon. I would have been more than happy to pay that additional amount for the phone if they had included a compatible Nothing charger in the box. Now I'm using a good quality Amazon basics charger, Nothing should start including a compatible charger in the box, or let the customer pick if they want a charger bundled in the box. Just like how they pick the storage space they want on the phone, charge the customer an additional 1k or 1.5k for the charger to be included in the box, so customer who actually need a charger would still have the option to get a phone with its compatible charger from the company instead of scouring through the internet for hours to find a reliable charger with good reviews that is compatible with the phone, just an unwanted tension/hassle in my opinion.
